{
	"nodes":[
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60001","type":"text","x":0,"y":-600,"width":500,"height":120,"text":"# Metric Container Alignment\n\nLayered precedence system for metric ownership across parser, dialect, user-plan, runtime, and user-entry layers.","color":"6"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60010","type":"group","x":-100,"y":-420,"width":700,"height":1680,"label":"Metric Precedence Stack (lowest ‚Üí highest)","color":"0"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60002","type":"text","x":0,"y":-380,"width":500,"height":200,"text":"## Layer 1: Parser (Tier 5)\n\n**Origin:** `parser`\n**Source:** Source text parsing\n\n- Base metrics from WOD script\n- `DurationMetric`, `RepMetric`, `EffortMetric`, etc.\n- Read-only baseline ‚Äî never modified by higher layers\n- Preserved in `rawMetrics` for debugging","color":"4"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60003","type":"text","x":0,"y":-140,"width":500,"height":220,"text":"## Layer 2: Dialect (Tier 3)\n\n**Origin:** `dialect`\n**Source:** `IDialect.analyze()` overrides\n\n**Operations:**\n- ‚úÖ **Add** new metrics (e.g., CrossFit scoring metric)\n- üîÑ **Replace** parser metrics with domain-specific versions\n- ‚ùå **Nullify** parser metrics that don't apply\n- ‚¨ÜÔ∏è **Promote** metrics for child inheritance","color":"3"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60004","type":"text","x":0,"y":120,"width":500,"height":220,"text":"## Layer 3: User-Plan (Tier 2)\n\n**Origin:** `user-plan`\n**Source:** User composition before execution\n\n**Operations:**\n- ‚úÖ **Add** personal target metrics\n- üîÑ **Replace** dialect defaults with personal goals\n- ‚ùå **Nullify** metrics not relevant to this session\n- üìù **Compose** multiple metrics into planned workout","color":"3"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60005","type":"text","x":0,"y":380,"width":500,"height":220,"text":"## Layer 4: Runtime (Tier 1)\n\n**Origin:** `runtime`, `tracked`, `analyzed`\n**Source:** Execution engine output\n\n**Operations:**\n- ‚úÖ **Add** execution-time metrics (elapsed, spans)\n- üîÑ **Override** projected metrics with actual values\n- üìä **Track** live metrics during execution\n- üì§ **Emit** results via `ReportOutputBehavior`","color":"5"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60006","type":"text","x":0,"y":640,"width":500,"height":220,"text":"## Layer 5: User-Entry (Tier 0)\n\n**Origin:** `user-entry`, `collected`, `execution`\n**Source:** Post-execution user corrections\n\n**Operations:**\n- ‚úÖ **Add** metrics the runtime didn't capture\n- üîÑ **Correct** runtime values (actual reps, actual weight)\n- ‚ùå **Nullify** erroneous runtime metrics\n- üìù **Annotate** with notes and observations","color":"1"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60007","type":"text","x":0,"y":920,"width":500,"height":140,"text":"## Resolution Output\n\n`MetricContainer.resolve()` ‚Üí For each `MetricType`, returns metric(s) from the **highest-precedence tier** present. Lower-tier originals preserved in `rawMetrics`.","color":"6"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60020","type":"text","x":700,"y":-380,"width":400,"height":160,"text":"### Parser Pipeline\n\n```\nSource Text\n  ‚Üí Chevrotain Tokenizer\n  ‚Üí timer.parser.ts\n  ‚Üí timer.visitor.ts\n  ‚Üí CodeStatement { metrics[] }\n```\n\nOrigin: `parser` (tier 5)","color":"4"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60021","type":"text","x":700,"y":-140,"width":400,"height":180,"text":"### Dialect Pipeline\n\n```\nCodeStatement\n  ‚Üí DialectRegistry.processAll()\n  ‚Üí IDialect.analyze()\n  ‚Üí DialectAnalysis {\n      hints[],\n      metricOverrides[],  ‚Üê NEW\n      nullifiedTypes[]    ‚Üê NEW\n    }\n```\n\nOrigin: `dialect` (tier 3)","color":"3"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60022","type":"text","x":700,"y":120,"width":400,"height":140,"text":"### User-Plan Pipeline\n\n```\nCodeStatement + dialect overrides\n  ‚Üí User customization UI\n  ‚Üí Add/replace/null metrics\n  ‚Üí Modified CodeStatement\n```\n\nOrigin: `user-plan` (tier 2)","color":"3"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60023","type":"text","x":700,"y":380,"width":400,"height":180,"text":"### Runtime Pipeline\n\n```\nCodeStatement\n  ‚Üí JitCompiler\n  ‚Üí BlockBuilder.build()\n  ‚Üí IRuntimeBlock {\n      memory: MemoryLocation[]\n      behaviors: IRuntimeBehavior[]\n    }\n  ‚Üí Behavior lifecycle\n  ‚Üí OutputStatement\n```\n\nOrigin: `runtime` (tier 1)","color":"5"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60024","type":"text","x":700,"y":640,"width":400,"height":140,"text":"### User-Entry Pipeline\n\n```\nOutputStatement\n  ‚Üí User data entry UI\n  ‚Üí Correct/add metrics\n  ‚Üí Final IMetricSource\n```\n\nOrigin: `user-entry` (tier 0)","color":"1"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60030","type":"text","x":-600,"y":-380,"width":400,"height":200,"text":"### Nullification\n\nAny layer can suppress a metric type from lower layers:\n\n```\nDialect: nullify(Rep)\n  ‚Üí Parser Rep metrics hidden\n  ‚Üí Dialect can add its own Rep\n\nUser-Plan: nullify(Distance)\n  ‚Üí Distance hidden from display\n  ‚Üí Runtime can still override\n```\n\nNull markers are origin-aware sentinel values.","color":"1"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60031","type":"text","x":-600,"y":-140,"width":400,"height":200,"text":"### Metric Preservation\n\nOverridden metrics are **never deleted**:\n\n```\nrawMetrics: [\n  Rep(21, origin=parser),\n  Rep(10, origin=dialect),\n  Rep(12, origin=user-plan)\n]\n\nresolve() ‚Üí Rep(12, origin=user-plan)\n```\n\nAll layers accessible via `MetricFilter.origins`.","color":"4"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60032","type":"text","x":-600,"y":120,"width":400,"height":200,"text":"### Promotion Across Layers\n\n`MetricPromotionBehavior` cascades metrics from parent to child blocks:\n\n```\nParent (dialect-origin Rep)\n  ‚Üì getPromotedFragments()\nChild receives Rep with\n  origin preserved as 'dialect'\n  ‚Üì child's own layers\n  can still override\n```\n\nOrigin-aware promotion works naturally.","color":"5"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60040","type":"text","x":-600,"y":380,"width":400,"height":260,"text":"### Precedence Table\n\n| Tier | Origin | Layer |\n|------|--------|-------|\n| 0 | `user-entry`, `collected`, `execution` | User corrections |\n| 1 | `runtime`, `tracked`, `analyzed` | Execution data |\n| 2 | `user-plan` | User composition |\n| 3 | `dialect`, `hinted` | Domain overrides |\n| 4 | `compiler` | JIT synthesis |\n| 5 | `parser` | Source text |\n\nLower tier number = higher precedence.","color":"6"},
		{"id":"a1b2c3d4e5f60050","type":"text","x":-600,"y":700,"width":400,"height":200,"text":"### Key Files to Modify\n\n- `src/core/models/Metric.ts` ‚Äî New origins\n- `src/core/utils/metricPrecedence.ts` ‚Äî 6-tier map\n- `src/core/models/MetricContainer.ts` ‚Äî Null support\n- `src/core/models/Dialect.ts` ‚Äî Metric overrides\n- `src/services/DialectRegistry.ts` ‚Äî Inject overrides\n- `src/core/contracts/IMetricSource.ts` ‚Äî Layer access","color":"0"}
	],
	"edges":[
		{"id":"e1f2a3b4c5d60001","fromNode":"a1b2c3d4e5f60001","fromSide":"bottom","toNode":"a1b2c3d4e5f60002","toSide":"top"},
